General.Name: Kiwetinohk Energy Corp
General.Description: Kiwetinohk Energy Corp., an energy transition company, engages in the development and production of natural gas in west-central Alberta. The company develops and operates renewable solar and wind power projects, and natural gas-fired power generation plants; produces hydrogen; produces and markets oil, condensate, carbon dioxide, and natural gas liquids. It also offers electricity, low emissions electricity, hydrogen, and carbon dioxide; and produces clean products from natural gas. The company was formerly known as Alberta Ltd. and has changed its name to Kiwetinohk Energy Corp. in 2021. Kiwetinohk Energy Corp. was formed in 2018 and is based in Calgary, Canada.
